Two businessmen on Monday appeared in a Magistrates’ Court in Ojo, Lagos, for allegedly stealing 1,500 empty crates of Trophy Beer. <img class="alignnone wp-image-1265514 size-large" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="Two businessmen in court for allegedly stealing 1,500 empty crates of trophy beer" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The police charged Sunday Michael,25, and Emeka Valentine, 39, both businessmen with conspiracy and theft. They, however, both pleaded not guilty to the charges. The prosecution counsel Mr Simon Uche alleged that the defendants stole 1,500 empty crates of Trophy Beer, belonging to Mr Peter Egodi, valued at N1.5 million. He was also alleged that they stole N146,000 belonging to Egodi. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of sections 287, 328 and 411 of the Criminal Laws of Lagos State. 2011. Magistrate A.A Adesanya admitted the defendants to bail in the sum of N200,000 each with two sureties each in like sum. He adjourned the case until Dec. 9 for mention. Vanguard Nigeria News  A 50-year-old man, Yusuf Ahmed, who allegedly stole 485 crates of beer, two cartons of Ground Malt and 222 empty crates of soft drinks, worth N2.4 million on Thursday appeared in a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. June 20, 2019 In "News" A 25-year-old truck driver working for the Nigeria Breweries PLC, Kelly Osang , who allegedly stole his employer’s 700 empty crates of different brands of beer valued at N1.4million, on Thursday appeared in an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court, Lagos. December 27, 2018 In "News" A 21-year-old man, Kamaru Kuye, who allegedly broke into a shop and stole goods valued at N220,800, on Thursday appeared in an Ebute Meta Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. December 27, 2018 In "News"